                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've always found it strange that our last single cast mana regen spell was Clarity 2, yet enchanters get KEI, Tranq, and then VoQ (group mana regen spells) within 6 levels of each other.
<br />

<br />
To be honest, I skipped Tranquility completely. The extra 2 mana regen it gives over KEI didn't make it worth the effort to cast, given it lasts 1/3rd as long as KEI. So I stuck with KEI until I got VoQ, as I'm sure quite a few people here did.
<br />

<br />
But last night I was raiding one of the HoH trials, and more then once during the night we had to rez in a fallen caster, who needed to be re-VoQ. Now each group cast of the spell drained a lot of mana, especially when 3 people were rezzed back at once, in 3 different groups. That's three casts of VoQ, which meant I was out of action for a while.
<br />

<br />
And it got me thinking. Why not make Tranquility a single target mana regen spell? Up the regen to 19 (a la voq), reduce the mana cost and casting time, and make it single target? This would be a decent upgrade, and would make Tranquility a useful spell again.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
